1 ($7,500.00) seventy-five thousand dollars ($75,000.00), the
2 same shall be let to the lowest responsible bidder, and the
3 commissioner shall advertise for sealed bids, by notice
4 published in some newspaper published in the county in
5 which the petition is filed, and may advertise in one (1)
6 or more newspapers published elsewhere. If there be no
7 newspaper published in the county in which the petition is
8 filed, they shall advertise in some newspaper published in
9 an adjoining county, which said notice shall particularly
10 set forth the time and place when and where the bids
11 advertised will be opened, the kind of work to be let and
12 the terms of payment. Said commissioners may continue the
13 letting from time to time, if in their judgment the same
14 shall be necessary, and shall reserve the right to reject
15 any and all bids. This section shall not be construed to
16 apply to the employment of superintendent, engineer,
17 attorney or other employee engaged in the general work of
18 the district.
19
20 41-7-813. Construction of irrigation works; cost
21 estimates; advertisement for bids; contracts.
22
