1 Before any district shall enter into any contract for the
2 construction, building, alteration, extension, or
3 improvement of any irrigation works, power plant or system,
4 or any part or section thereof for the use of the district,
5 or for the purchase of any materials, machinery, or
6 apparatus, such district shall cause estimates of the cost
7 thereof to be made by some competent engineer or engineers
8 and if such estimated cost shall exceed the sum of one
9 thousand dollars ($1,000.00) twenty thousand dollars
10 ($20,000.00) no such contract shall be entered into for a
11 price, cost or consideration exceeding such estimate nor
12 without advertising for sealed bids. Prior to such
13 advertisement, plans and specifications for the proposed
14 construction work or materials shall be prepared and filed
15 at the principal office or place of business of the
16 district. Such advertisement shall be inserted for three
17 (3) consecutive issues, with not less than twenty (20) days
18 intervening between the first and last publication dates,
19 in one (1) or more newspapers of general circulation in the
20 district and, in the discretion of the board of directors
21 of the district, in such additional newspapers or trade or
22 technical periodicals as may be selected by the board in
23 order to give proper notice of the receiving of bids. Such
