1 advertisement shall designate the nature of the
2 construction work proposed to be done or materials proposed
3 to be purchased; that the plans and specifications therefor
4 may be inspected at the office of the district, giving the
5 location thereof, and shall designate the time within which
6 bids shall be filed and the date, hour and place the same
7 shall be opened. The board of directors of the district,
8 with the assistance of the state engineer, whose duty it
9 shall be to supervise such lettings, may let the contract
10 for such work or materials to the lowest responsible
11 bidder, or, in the sole discretion of the board, all bids
12 tendered may be rejected and readvertisement for bids made
13 in the manner, form and time in this section provided. No
14 such contract shall be valid nor shall any money of the
15 district be expended thereunder unless advertisement and
16 letting shall have been had as in this section provided.
17 Such contract shall provide that wherever possible workmen
18 who are citizens of Wyoming shall be employed by the
19 contractor. All provisions of W.S. 16-6-112 through
20 16-6-115, with reference to contractor's bonds, shall be
21 applicable and effective as to any contract let pursuant to
22 the provisions of this act; provided further, that if all
23 or a portion of the cost of the proposed works is to be met
